Japan Beats New Zealand 2-1 in Women’s World Cup Game; England, Mexico Tie

-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 
2011-06-27T18:40:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-27/japan-defeats-new-zealand-2-1-in-women-s-world-cup-soccer-match-in-germany.html
Japan  won its opening match in
soccer’s Women’s World Cup today while England and Mexico tied.  Japan beat  New Zealand  2-1 in Bochum with goals by Yuki
Nagasato and Aya Miyama. Amber Hearn got New Zealand’s goal.  In the other game in Group B, Fara Williams’s goal for
England was leveled by Monica Ocampo, on a mistake by goalkeeper
Karen Bardsley, in a 1-1 draw in Wolfsburg.  The results leave Japan on  three points , England and Mexico
on one, and New Zealand on none.  Yesterday, in Group A, Germany opened its title defense
with a 2-1 win against Canada. France defeated Nigeria 1-0 in
the other match on the first day of the tournament.  The 16 teams are split into four groups with the top two in
each progressing to the quarterfinals. The final of the four-
yearly  soccer tournament  is on July 17.  Tomorrow, two-time World Cup winner the U.S. plays North
Korea in Dresden and Colombia meets Sweden in Leverkusen, in the
opening matches of Group C.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty in London at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 